defs.name: to_shortest_str
defs.value: fn <'a, T, F> (mut format_shortest: F, v: T, sign: Sign, frac_digits: usize, _upper: bool, buf: &'a mut [u8], parts: &'a mut [Part<'a>]) -> Formatted<'a>
defs.docs:
Formats the given floating point number into the decimal form with at least
 given number of fractional digits. The result is stored to the supplied parts
 array while utilizing given byte buffer as a scratch. `upper` is currently
 unused but left for the future decision to change the case of non-finite values,
 i.e., `inf` and `nan`. The first part to be rendered is always a `Part::Sign`
 (which can be an empty string if no sign is rendered).

defs.name: to_shortest_exp_str
defs.value: fn <'a, T, F> (mut format_shortest: F, v: T, sign: Sign, dec_bounds: (i16, i16), upper: bool, buf: &'a mut [u8], parts: &'a mut [Part<'a>]) -> Formatted<'a>
defs.docs:
Formats the given floating point number into the decimal form or
 the exponential form, depending on the resulting exponent. The result is
 stored to the supplied parts array while utilizing given byte buffer
 as a scratch. `upper` is used to determine the case of non-finite values
 (`inf` and `nan`) or the case of the exponent prefix (`e` or `E`).
 The first part to be rendered is always a `Part::Sign` (which can be
 an empty string if no sign is rendered).

defs.name: to_exact_exp_str
defs.value: fn <'a, T, F> (mut format_exact: F, v: T, sign: Sign, ndigits: usize, upper: bool, buf: &'a mut [u8], parts: &'a mut [Part<'a>]) -> Formatted<'a>
defs.docs:
Formats given floating point number into the exponential form with
 exactly given number of significant digits. The result is stored to
 the supplied parts array while utilizing given byte buffer as a scratch.
 `upper` is used to determine the case of the exponent prefix (`e` or `E`).
 The first part to be rendered is always a `Part::Sign` (which can be
 an empty string if no sign is rendered).

defs.name: to_exact_fixed_str
defs.value: fn <'a, T, F> (mut format_exact: F, v: T, sign: Sign, frac_digits: usize, _upper: bool, buf: &'a mut [u8], parts: &'a mut [Part<'a>]) -> Formatted<'a>
defs.docs:
Formats given floating point number into the decimal form with exactly
 given number of fractional digits. The result is stored to the supplied parts
 array while utilizing given byte buffer as a scratch. `upper` is currently

 i.e., `inf` and `nan`. The first part to be rendered is always a `Part::Sign`

defs.name: rawfp
defs.docs:
Bit fiddling on positive IEEE 754 floats. Negative numbers aren't and needn't be handled.
 Normal floating point numbers have a canonical representation as (frac, exp) such that the
 value is 2<sup>exp</sup> * (1 + sum(frac[N-i] / 2<sup>i</sup>)) where N is the number of bits.
 Subnormals are slightly different and weird, but the same principle applies.

defs.name: full_add
defs.value: fn (self, other: Self, carry: bool) -> (bool, Self)
defs.docs:
Returns `(carry', v')` such that `carry' * 2^W + v' = self + other + carry`,
 where `W` is the number of bits in `Self`.

defs.name: full_mul
defs.value: fn (self, other: Self, carry: Self) -> (Self, Self)
defs.docs:
Returns `(carry', v')` such that `carry' * 2^W + v' = self * other + carry`,
 where `W` is the number of bits in `Self`.

defs.name: full_mul_add
defs.value: fn (self, other: Self, other2: Self, carry: Self) -> (Self, Self)
defs.docs:
Returns `(carry', v')` such that `carry' * 2^W + v' = self * other + other2 + carry`,
 where `W` is the number of bits in `Self`.

defs.name: full_div_rem
defs.value: fn (self, other: Self, borrow: Self) -> (Self, Self)
defs.docs:
Returns `(quo, rem)` such that `borrow * 2^W + self = quo * other + rem`
 and `0 <= rem < other`, where `W` is the number of bits in `Self`.

defs.name: is_ascii_whitespace
defs.docs:
Checks if the value is an ASCII whitespace character:
 U+0020 SPACE, U+0009 HORIZONTAL TAB, U+000A LINE FEED,
 U+000C FORM FEED, or U+000D CARRIAGE RETURN.

defs.name: is_ascii_control
defs.docs:
Checks if the value is an ASCII control character:
 U+0000 NUL ..= U+001F UNIT SEPARATOR, or U+007F DELETE.
 Note that most ASCII whitespace characters are control
 characters, but SPACE is not.

defs.name: atomic_cxchg
defs.value: fn <T> (dst: *mut T, old: T, src: T) -> (T, bool)
defs.docs:
Stores a value if the current value is the same as the `old` value.
 The stabilized version of this intrinsic is available on the
 `std::sync::atomic` types via the `compare_exchange` method by passing
 [`Ordering::SeqCst`](../../std/sync/atomic/enum.Ordering.html)
 as both the `success` and `failure` parameters. For example,
 [`AtomicBool::compare_exchange`][compare_exchange].

 characteristics.

defs.name: exact_div
defs.docs:
Performs an exact division, resulting in undefined behavior where
 `x % y != 0` or `y == 0` or `x == T::min_value() && y == -1`

defs.name: unchecked_div
defs.docs:
Performs an unchecked division, resulting in undefined behavior
 where y = 0 or x = `T::min_value()` and y = -1

defs.name: unchecked_rem
defs.docs:
Returns the remainder of an unchecked division, resulting in
 undefined behavior where y = 0 or x = `T::min_value()` and y = -1

defs.name: unchecked_shl
defs.docs:
Performs an unchecked left shift, resulting in undefined behavior when
 y < 0 or y >= N, where N is the width of T in bits.

defs.name: unchecked_shr
defs.docs:
Performs an unchecked right shift, resulting in undefined behavior when
 y < 0 or y >= N, where N is the width of T in bits.

defs.name: unchecked_add
defs.docs:
Returns the result of an unchecked addition, resulting in
 undefined behavior when `x + y > T::max_value()` or `x + y < T::min_value()`.

defs.name: unchecked_sub
defs.docs:
Returns the result of an unchecked substraction, resulting in
 undefined behavior when `x - y > T::max_value()` or `x - y < T::min_value()`.

defs.name: unchecked_mul
defs.docs:
Returns the result of an unchecked multiplication, resulting in
 undefined behavior when `x * y > T::max_value()` or `x * y < T::min_value()`.

defs.name: mem

defs.name: ManuallyDrop
defs.docs: A wrapper to inhibit compiler from automatically calling `T`s destructor.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Wrap a value to be manually dropped.

defs.name: into_inner
defs.docs: Extracts the value from the `ManuallyDrop` container.

defs.name: take
defs.docs: Takes the contained value out.

attributes.value:
must_use =
      "if you don't need the value, you can use `ManuallyDrop::drop` instead"

defs.name: drop
defs.docs: Manually drops the contained value.

defs.name: MaybeUninit
defs.docs: A wrapper type to construct uninitialized instances of `T`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Creates a new `MaybeUninit<T>` initialized with the given value.
 It is safe to call [`assume_init`] on the return value of this function.

defs.name: uninit
defs.docs: Creates a new `MaybeUninit<T>` in an uninitialized state.

defs.name: zeroed
defs.docs:
Creates a new `MaybeUninit<T>` in an uninitialized state, with the memory being
 filled with `0` bytes. It depends on `T` whether that already makes for
 proper initialization. For example, `MaybeUninit<usize>::zeroed()` is initialized,
 but `MaybeUninit<&'static i32>::zeroed()` is not because references must not
 be null.

defs.name: write
defs.docs:
Sets the value of the `MaybeUninit<T>`. This overwrites any previous value
 without dropping it, so be careful not to use this twice unless you want to
 skip running the destructor. For your convenience, this also returns a mutable
 reference to the (now safely initialized) contents of `self`.

defs.name: as_ptr
defs.docs:
Gets a pointer to the contained value. Reading from this pointer or turning it
 into a reference is undefined behavior unless the `MaybeUninit<T>` is initialized.
 Writing to memory that this pointer (non-transitively) points to is undefined behavior
 (except inside an `UnsafeCell<T>`).

defs.name: as_mut_ptr
defs.docs:
Gets a mutable pointer to the contained value. Reading from this pointer or turning it
 into a reference is undefined behavior unless the `MaybeUninit<T>` is initialized.

defs.name: assume_init
defs.docs:
Extracts the value from the `MaybeUninit<T>` container. This is a great way
 to ensure that the data will get dropped, because the resulting `T` is
 subject to the usual drop handling.

defs.name: read
defs.docs:
Reads the value from the `MaybeUninit<T>` container. The resulting `T` is subject
 to the usual drop handling.

defs.name: get_ref
defs.docs: Gets a reference to the contained value.

defs.name: get_mut
defs.docs: Gets a mutable reference to the contained value.

defs.name: first_ptr
defs.docs: Gets a pointer to the first element of the array.

defs.name: first_ptr_mut
defs.docs: Gets a mutable pointer to the first element of the array.

defs.name: forget
defs.docs: Takes ownership and "forgets" about the value **without running its destructor**.

defs.name: forget_unsized
defs.docs: Like [`forget`], but also accepts unsized values.

defs.name: size_of

defs.name: Shl
defs.docs:
The left shift operator `<<`. Note that because this trait is implemented
 for all integer types with multiple right-hand-side types, Rust's type
 checker has special handling for `_ << _`, setting the result type for
 integer operations to the type of the left-hand-side operand. This means
 that though `a << b` and `a.shl(b)` are one and the same from an evaluation
 standpoint, they are different when it comes to type inference.

defs.name: Release
defs.docs:
When coupled with a store, all previous operations become ordered
 before any load of this value with [`Acquire`] (or stronger) ordering.
 In particular, all previous writes become visible to all threads
 that perform an [`Acquire`] (or stronger) load of this value.

defs.name: Acquire
defs.docs:
When coupled with a load, if the loaded value was written by a store operation with
 [`Release`] (or stronger) ordering, then all subsequent operations
 become ordered after that store. In particular, all subsequent loads will see data
 written before the store.

defs.name: AcqRel
defs.docs:
Has the effects of both [`Acquire`] and [`Release`] together:
 For loads it uses [`Acquire`] ordering. For stores it uses the [`Release`] ordering.

defs.name: SeqCst
defs.docs:
Like [`Acquire`]/[`Release`]/[`AcqRel`] (for load, store, and load-with-store
 operations, respectively) with the additional guarantee that all threads see all
 sequentially consistent operations in the same order.

                            note =

                         on(_Self = "[std::ops::RangeFrom<Idx>; 1]",
                            label =
                                "if you meant to iterate from a value onwards, remove the square brackets",
                            note =
                                "`[start..]` is an array of one `RangeFrom`; you might have meant to have a \
              `RangeFrom` without the brackets: `start..`, keeping in mind that iterating over an \
              unbounded iterator will run forever unless you `break` or `return` from within the \
              loop"),
                         on(_Self = "[std::ops::RangeTo<Idx>; 1]",
                            label =
                                "if you meant to iterate until a value, remove the square brackets and add a \
               starting value",
                            note =
                                "`[..end]` is an array of one `RangeTo`; you might have meant to have a bounded \
              `Range` without the brackets: `0..end`"),
                         on(_Self = "[std::ops::RangeInclusive<Idx>; 1]",
                            label =
                                "if you meant to iterate between two values, remove the square brackets",
                            note =
                                "`[start..=end]` is an array of one `RangeInclusive`; you might have meant to have a \
              `RangeInclusive` without the brackets: `start..=end`"),
                         on(_Self = "[std::ops::RangeToInclusive<Idx>; 1]",
                            label =
                                "if you meant to iterate until a value (including it), remove the square brackets \
               and add a starting value",
                            note =
                                "`[..=end]` is an array of one `RangeToInclusive`; you might have meant to have a \
              bounded `RangeInclusive` without the brackets: `0..=end`"),
                         on(_Self = "std::ops::RangeTo<Idx>",
                            label =
                                "if you meant to iterate until a value, add a starting value",
                            note =
                                "`..end` is a `RangeTo`, which cannot be iterated on; you might have meant to have a \
              bounded `Range`: `0..end`"),
                         on(_Self = "std::ops::RangeToInclusive<Idx>",
                            label =
                                "if you meant to iterate until a value (including it), add a starting value",
                            note =
                                "`..=end` is a `RangeToInclusive`, which cannot be iterated on; you might have meant \
              to have a bounded `RangeInclusive`: `0..=end`"),
                         on(_Self = "&str",
                            label =
                                "`{Self}` is not an iterator; try calling `.chars()` or `.bytes()`"),
                         on(_Self = "std::string::String",
                            label =
                                "`{Self}` is not an iterator; try calling `.chars()` or `.bytes()`"),
                         on(_Self = "[]",
                            label =

 not contained in the subslices.

defs.name: rotate_left
defs.docs:
Rotates the slice in-place such that the first `mid` elements of the
 slice move to the end while the last `self.len() - mid` elements move to
 the front. After calling `rotate_left`, the element previously at index
 `mid` will become the first element in the slice.

defs.name: rotate_right
defs.docs:
Rotates the slice in-place such that the first `self.len() - k`
 elements of the slice move to the end while the last `k` elements move
 to the front. After calling `rotate_right`, the element previously at
 index `self.len() - k` will become the first element in the slice.

 ensure that each instance is given its requested size and
 alignment. On success, returns `(k, offs)` where `k` is the
 layout of the array and `offs` is the distance between the start
 of each element in the array.

defs.name: extend
defs.value: fn (&self, next: Self) -> Result<(Self, usize), LayoutErr>
defs.docs:
Creates a layout describing the record for `self` followed by
 `next`, including any necessary padding to ensure that `next`
 will be properly aligned. Note that the result layout will
 satisfy the alignment properties of both `self` and `next`.

defs.name: repeat_packed
defs.docs:
Creates a layout describing the record for `n` instances of
 `self`, with no padding between each instance.

defs.name: extend_packed
defs.docs:
Creates a layout describing the record for `self` followed by
 `next` with no additional padding between the two. Since no
 padding is inserted, the alignment of `next` is irrelevant,
 and is not incorporated *at all* into the resulting layout.

defs.name: array
defs.docs: Creates a layout describing the record for a `[T; n]`.

defs.name: LayoutErr
defs.docs:

defs.name: AllocErr
defs.docs:

defs.name: CannotReallocInPlace
defs.docs:
The `CannotReallocInPlace` error is used when `grow_in_place` or
 `shrink_in_place` were unable to reuse the given memory block for

defs.name: alloc_zeroed

defs.name: realloc
defs.value: fn (&self, ptr: *mut u8, layout: Layout, new_size: usize) -> *mut u8
defs.docs:
Shrink or grow a block of memory to the given `new_size`.
 The block is described by the given `ptr` pointer and `layout`.

defs.name: Alloc
defs.docs:
An implementation of `Alloc` can allocate, reallocate, and
 deallocate arbitrary blocks of data described via `Layout`.

defs.name: alloc
defs.value: fn (&mut self, layout: Layout) -> Result<NonNull<u8>, AllocErr>
defs.docs:

defs.name: dealloc
defs.value: fn (&mut self, ptr: NonNull<u8>, layout: Layout) -> ()
defs.docs: Deallocate the memory referenced by `ptr`.

defs.name: usable_size
defs.docs:
Returns bounds on the guaranteed usable size of a successful

defs.name: realloc
defs.value: fn (&mut self, ptr: NonNull<u8>, layout: Layout, new_size: usize) -> Result<NonNull<u8>, AllocErr>
defs.docs:
Returns a pointer suitable for holding data described by
 a new layout with `layout`s alignment and a size given
 by `new_size`. To
 accomplish this, this may extend or shrink the allocation
 referenced by `ptr` to fit the new layout.

defs.name: alloc_zeroed
defs.value: fn (&mut self, layout: Layout) -> Result<NonNull<u8>, AllocErr>
defs.docs:
Behaves like `alloc`, but also ensures that the contents

defs.name: _mm_cmpeq_ss
defs.docs:
Compares the lowest `f32` of both inputs for equality. The lowest 32 bits of
 the result will be `0xffffffff` if the two inputs are equal, or `0`
 otherwise. The upper 96 bits of the result are the upper 96 bits of `a`.

defs.name: _mm_cmplt_ss
defs.docs:
Compares the lowest `f32` of both inputs for less than. The lowest 32 bits
 of the result will be `0xffffffff` if `a.extract(0)` is less than
 `b.extract(0)`, or `0` otherwise. The upper 96 bits of the result are the
 upper 96 bits of `a`.

defs.name: _mm_cmple_ss
defs.docs:
Compares the lowest `f32` of both inputs for less than or equal. The lowest
 32 bits of the result will be `0xffffffff` if `a.extract(0)` is less than
 or equal `b.extract(0)`, or `0` otherwise. The upper 96 bits of the result
 are the upper 96 bits of `a`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpgt_ss
defs.docs:
Compares the lowest `f32` of both inputs for greater than. The lowest 32
 bits of the result will be `0xffffffff` if `a.extract(0)` is greater
 than `b.extract(0)`, or `0` otherwise. The upper 96 bits of the result
 are the upper 96 bits of `a`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpge_ss
defs.docs:
Compares the lowest `f32` of both inputs for greater than or equal. The
 lowest 32 bits of the result will be `0xffffffff` if `a.extract(0)` is
 greater than or equal `b.extract(0)`, or `0` otherwise. The upper 96 bits
 of the result are the upper 96 bits of `a`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpneq_ss
defs.docs:
Compares the lowest `f32` of both inputs for inequality. The lowest 32 bits
 of the result will be `0xffffffff` if `a.extract(0)` is not equal to
 `b.extract(0)`, or `0` otherwise. The upper 96 bits of the result are the
 upper 96 bits of `a`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpnlt_ss
defs.docs:
Compares the lowest `f32` of both inputs for not-less-than. The lowest 32
 bits of the result will be `0xffffffff` if `a.extract(0)` is not less than
 `b.extract(0)`, or `0` otherwise. The upper 96 bits of the result are the
 upper 96 bits of `a`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpnle_ss
defs.docs:
Compares the lowest `f32` of both inputs for not-less-than-or-equal. The
 lowest 32 bits of the result will be `0xffffffff` if `a.extract(0)` is not
 less than or equal to `b.extract(0)`, or `0` otherwise. The upper 96 bits
 of the result are the upper 96 bits of `a`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpngt_ss
defs.docs:
Compares the lowest `f32` of both inputs for not-greater-than. The lowest 32
 bits of the result will be `0xffffffff` if `a.extract(0)` is not greater
 than `b.extract(0)`, or `0` otherwise. The upper 96 bits of the result are
 the upper 96 bits of `a`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpnge_ss
defs.docs:
Compares the lowest `f32` of both inputs for not-greater-than-or-equal. The
 lowest 32 bits of the result will be `0xffffffff` if `a.extract(0)` is not
 greater than or equal to `b.extract(0)`, or `0` otherwise. The upper 96
 bits of the result are the upper 96 bits of `a`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpord_ss
defs.docs:
Checks if the lowest `f32` of both inputs are ordered. The lowest 32 bits of
 the result will be `0xffffffff` if neither of `a.extract(0)` or
 `b.extract(0)` is a NaN, or `0` otherwise. The upper 96 bits of the result
 are the upper 96 bits of `a`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpunord_ss
defs.docs:
Checks if the lowest `f32` of both inputs are unordered. The lowest 32 bits
 of the result will be `0xffffffff` if any of `a.extract(0)` or
 `b.extract(0)` is a NaN, or `0` otherwise. The upper 96 bits of the result
 are the upper 96 bits of `a`.

defs.docs:

 The result in the output vector will be `0xffffffff` if the input element

defs.name: _mm_cmple_ps
defs.docs:

 The result in the output vector will be `0xffffffff` if the input element

 otherwise.

defs.name: _mm_cmpgt_ps
defs.docs:
Compares each of the four floats in `a` to the corresponding element in `b`.
 The result in the output vector will be `0xffffffff` if the input element
 in `a` is greater than the corresponding element in `b`, or `0` otherwise.

defs.name: _mm_cmpge_ps
defs.docs:

defs.name: _mm_cmpnlt_ps

defs.name: _mm_cmpnle_ps

defs.name: _mm_cmpngt_ps
defs.docs:

defs.name: _mm_cmpnge_ps
defs.docs:
Compares each of the four floats in `a` to the corresponding element in `b`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpord_ps
defs.docs:

 Returns four floats that have one of two possible bit patterns. The element

defs.name: _mm_cmpunord_ps
defs.docs:

 Returns four floats that have one of two possible bit patterns. The element

 `b` are unordered (i.e., at least on of them is a NaN), or 0 otherwise.

Shifts packed 16-bit integers in `a` right by `count` while shifting in
 zeros.

defs.name: _mm_srli_epi32
defs.docs:
Shifts packed 32-bit integers in `a` right by `imm8` while shifting in
 zeros.

defs.name: _mm_srl_epi32
defs.docs:
Shifts packed 32-bit integers in `a` right by `count` while shifting in
 zeros.

defs.name: _mm_srli_epi64
defs.docs:
Shifts packed 64-bit integers in `a` right by `imm8` while shifting in
 zeros.

defs.name: _mm_srl_epi64
defs.docs:
Shifts packed 64-bit integers in `a` right by `count` while shifting in
 zeros.

defs.name: _mm_and_si128
defs.docs:
Computes the bitwise AND of 128 bits (representing integer data) in `a` and
 `b`.

defs.name: _mm_andnot_si128
defs.docs:
Computes the bitwise NOT of 128 bits (representing integer data) in `a` and
 then AND with `b`.

defs.name: _mm_or_si128
defs.docs:
Computes the bitwise OR of 128 bits (representing integer data) in `a` and
 `b`.

defs.name: _mm_xor_si128
defs.docs:
Computes the bitwise XOR of 128 bits (representing integer data) in `a` and
 `b`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpeq_epi8
defs.docs: Compares packed 8-bit integers in `a` and `b` for equality.

defs.name: _mm_cmpeq_epi16
defs.docs: Compares packed 16-bit integers in `a` and `b` for equality.

defs.name: _mm_cmpeq_epi32
defs.docs: Compares packed 32-bit integers in `a` and `b` for equality.

defs.name: _mm_cmpgt_epi8
defs.docs: Compares packed 8-bit integers in `a` and `b` for greater-than.

defs.name: _mm_cmpgt_epi16
defs.docs: Compares packed 16-bit integers in `a` and `b` for greater-than.

defs.name: _mm_cmpgt_epi32
defs.docs: Compares packed 32-bit integers in `a` and `b` for greater-than.

defs.name: _mm_cmplt_epi8
defs.docs: Compares packed 8-bit integers in `a` and `b` for less-than.

defs.name: _mm_cmplt_epi16
defs.docs: Compares packed 16-bit integers in `a` and `b` for less-than.

defs.name: _mm_cmplt_epi32
defs.docs: Compares packed 32-bit integers in `a` and `b` for less-than.

defs.name: _mm_cvtepi32_pd
defs.docs:
Converts the lower two packed 32-bit integers in `a` to packed
 double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements.

defs.name: _mm_cvtsi32_sd
defs.docs:
Returns `a` with its lower element replaced by `b` after converting it to
 an `f64`.

defs.name: _mm_cvtepi32_ps
defs.docs:
Converts packed 32-bit integers in `a` to packed single-precision (32-bit)
 floating-point elements.

defs.name: _mm_cvtps_epi32
defs.docs:
Converts packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements in `a`
 to packed 32-bit integers.

defs.name: _mm_cvtsi32_si128
defs.docs:
Returns a vector whose lowest element is `a` and all higher elements are
 `0`.

defs.name: _mm_cvtsi128_si32
defs.docs: Returns the lowest element of `a`.

defs.name: _mm_set_epi64x
defs.docs:
Sets packed 64-bit integers with the supplied values, from highest to
 lowest.

defs.name: _mm_set_epi32
defs.docs: Sets packed 32-bit integers with the supplied values.

defs.name: _mm_set_epi16
defs.docs: Sets packed 16-bit integers with the supplied values.

defs.name: _mm_set_epi8
defs.docs: Sets packed 8-bit integers with the supplied values.

defs.name: _mm_set1_epi64x
defs.docs: Broadcasts 64-bit integer `a` to all elements.

defs.name: _mm_set1_epi32
defs.docs: Broadcasts 32-bit integer `a` to all elements.

defs.name: _mm_set1_epi16
defs.docs: Broadcasts 16-bit integer `a` to all elements.

defs.name: _mm_set1_epi8
defs.docs: Broadcasts 8-bit integer `a` to all elements.

defs.name: _mm_setr_epi32
defs.docs: Sets packed 32-bit integers with the supplied values in reverse order.

defs.name: _mm_setr_epi16
defs.docs: Sets packed 16-bit integers with the supplied values in reverse order.

defs.name: _mm_setr_epi8
defs.docs: Sets packed 8-bit integers with the supplied values in reverse order.

defs.name: _mm_setzero_si128
defs.docs: Returns a vector with all elements set to zero.

defs.name: _mm_loadl_epi64
defs.docs: Loads 64-bit integer from memory into first element of returned vector.

defs.name: _mm_load_si128
defs.docs: Loads 128-bits of integer data from memory into a new vector.

defs.name: _mm_loadu_si128
defs.docs: Loads 128-bits of integer data from memory into a new vector.

defs.name: _mm_maskmoveu_si128
defs.docs:
Conditionally store 8-bit integer elements from `a` into memory using
 `mask`.

defs.name: _mm_store_si128
defs.docs: Stores 128-bits of integer data from `a` into memory.

defs.name: _mm_storeu_si128
defs.docs: Stores 128-bits of integer data from `a` into memory.

defs.name: _mm_storel_epi64
defs.docs: Stores the lower 64-bit integer `a` to a memory location.

defs.name: _mm_stream_si128
defs.docs:
Stores a 128-bit integer vector to a 128-bit aligned memory location.
 To minimize caching, the data is flagged as non-temporal (unlikely to be
 used again soon).

defs.name: _mm_stream_si32
defs.docs:
Stores a 32-bit integer value in the specified memory location.
 To minimize caching, the data is flagged as non-temporal (unlikely to be
 used again soon).

defs.name: _mm_move_epi64
defs.docs:
Returns a vector where the low element is extracted from `a` and its upper
 element is zero.

defs.name: _mm_packs_epi16
defs.docs:
Converts packed 16-bit integers from `a` and `b` to packed 8-bit integers
 using signed saturation.

defs.name: _mm_packs_epi32
defs.docs:
Converts packed 32-bit integers from `a` and `b` to packed 16-bit integers
 using signed saturation.

defs.name: _mm_packus_epi16
defs.docs:
Converts packed 16-bit integers from `a` and `b` to packed 8-bit integers
 using unsigned saturation.

defs.name: _mm_extract_epi16
defs.docs: Returns the `imm8` element of `a`.

defs.name: _mm_insert_epi16
defs.docs: Returns a new vector where the `imm8` element of `a` is replaced with `i`.

defs.name: _mm_movemask_epi8
defs.docs: Returns a mask of the most significant bit of each element in `a`.

defs.name: _mm_shuffle_epi32
defs.docs: Shuffles 32-bit integers in `a` using the control in `imm8`.

defs.name: _mm_shufflehi_epi16
defs.docs:
Shuffles 16-bit integers in the high 64 bits of `a` using the control in
 `imm8`.

defs.name: _mm_shufflelo_epi16
defs.docs:
Shuffles 16-bit integers in the low 64 bits of `a` using the control in
 `imm8`.

defs.name: _mm_unpackhi_epi8
defs.docs: Unpacks and interleave 8-bit integers from the high half of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_unpackhi_epi16
defs.docs: Unpacks and interleave 16-bit integers from the high half of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_unpackhi_epi32
defs.docs: Unpacks and interleave 32-bit integers from the high half of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_unpackhi_epi64
defs.docs: Unpacks and interleave 64-bit integers from the high half of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_unpacklo_epi8
defs.docs: Unpacks and interleave 8-bit integers from the low half of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_unpacklo_epi16
defs.docs: Unpacks and interleave 16-bit integers from the low half of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_unpacklo_epi32
defs.docs: Unpacks and interleave 32-bit integers from the low half of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_unpacklo_epi64
defs.docs: Unpacks and interleave 64-bit integers from the low half of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_add_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by the sum of the
 low elements of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_add_pd
defs.docs:
Adds packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements in `a` and
 `b`.

defs.name: _mm_div_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by the result of
 diving the lower element of `a` by the lower element of `b`.

defs.name: _mm_div_pd
defs.docs:
Divide packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements in `a` by
 packed elements in `b`.

defs.name: _mm_max_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by the maximum
 of the lower elements of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_max_pd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the maximum values from corresponding elements in
 `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_min_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by the minimum
 of the lower elements of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_min_pd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the minimum values from corresponding elements in
 `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_mul_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by multiplying the
 low elements of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_mul_pd
defs.docs:
Multiplies packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements in `a`
 and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_sqrt_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by the square
 root of the lower element `b`.

defs.name: _mm_sqrt_pd
defs.docs: Returns a new vector with the square root of each of the values in `a`.

defs.name: _mm_sub_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by subtracting the
 low element by `b` from the low element of `a`.

defs.name: _mm_sub_pd
defs.docs:
Subtract packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements in `b`
 from `a`.

defs.name: _mm_and_pd
defs.docs:
Computes the bitwise AND of packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point
 elements in `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_andnot_pd
defs.docs: Computes the bitwise NOT of `a` and then AND with `b`.

defs.name: _mm_or_pd
defs.docs: Computes the bitwise OR of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_xor_pd
defs.docs: Computes the bitwise OR of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpeq_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by the equality
 comparison of the lower elements of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_cmplt_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by the less-than
 comparison of the lower elements of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_cmple_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by the
 less-than-or-equal comparison of the lower elements of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpgt_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by the
 greater-than comparison of the lower elements of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpge_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by the
 greater-than-or-equal comparison of the lower elements of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpord_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by the result
 of comparing both of the lower elements of `a` and `b` to `NaN`. If
 neither are equal to `NaN` then `0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF` is used and `0`
 otherwise.

defs.name: _mm_cmpunord_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by the result of
 comparing both of the lower elements of `a` and `b` to `NaN`. If either is
 equal to `NaN` then `0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF` is used and `0` otherwise.

defs.name: _mm_cmpneq_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by the not-equal
 comparison of the lower elements of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpnlt_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by the
 not-less-than comparison of the lower elements of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpnle_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by the
 not-less-than-or-equal comparison of the lower elements of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpngt_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by the
 not-greater-than comparison of the lower elements of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpnge_sd
defs.docs:
Returns a new vector with the low element of `a` replaced by the
 not-greater-than-or-equal comparison of the lower elements of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpeq_pd
defs.docs: Compares corresponding elements in `a` and `b` for equality.

defs.name: _mm_cmplt_pd
defs.docs: Compares corresponding elements in `a` and `b` for less-than.

defs.name: _mm_cmple_pd
defs.docs: Compares corresponding elements in `a` and `b` for less-than-or-equal

defs.name: _mm_cmpgt_pd
defs.docs: Compares corresponding elements in `a` and `b` for greater-than.

defs.name: _mm_cmpge_pd
defs.docs: Compares corresponding elements in `a` and `b` for greater-than-or-equal.

defs.name: _mm_cmpord_pd
defs.docs: Compares corresponding elements in `a` and `b` to see if neither is `NaN`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpunord_pd
defs.docs: Compares corresponding elements in `a` and `b` to see if either is `NaN`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpneq_pd
defs.docs: Compares corresponding elements in `a` and `b` for not-equal.

defs.name: _mm_cmpnlt_pd
defs.docs: Compares corresponding elements in `a` and `b` for not-less-than.

defs.name: _mm_cmpnle_pd
defs.docs: Compares corresponding elements in `a` and `b` for not-less-than-or-equal.

defs.name: _mm_cmpngt_pd
defs.docs: Compares corresponding elements in `a` and `b` for not-greater-than.

defs.name: _mm_cmpnge_pd
defs.docs:
Compares corresponding elements in `a` and `b` for
 not-greater-than-or-equal.

defs.name: _mm_comieq_sd
defs.docs: Compares the lower element of `a` and `b` for equality.

defs.name: _mm_comilt_sd
defs.docs: Compares the lower element of `a` and `b` for less-than.

defs.name: _mm_comile_sd
defs.docs: Compares the lower element of `a` and `b` for less-than-or-equal.

defs.name: _mm_comigt_sd
defs.docs: Compares the lower element of `a` and `b` for greater-than.

defs.name: _mm_comige_sd
defs.docs: Compares the lower element of `a` and `b` for greater-than-or-equal.

defs.name: _mm_comineq_sd
defs.docs: Compares the lower element of `a` and `b` for not-equal.

defs.name: _mm_ucomieq_sd
defs.docs: Compares the lower element of `a` and `b` for equality.

defs.name: _mm_ucomilt_sd
defs.docs: Compares the lower element of `a` and `b` for less-than.

defs.name: _mm_ucomile_sd
defs.docs: Compares the lower element of `a` and `b` for less-than-or-equal.

defs.name: _mm_ucomigt_sd
defs.docs: Compares the lower element of `a` and `b` for greater-than.

defs.name: _mm_ucomige_sd
defs.docs: Compares the lower element of `a` and `b` for greater-than-or-equal.

defs.name: _mm_ucomineq_sd
defs.docs: Compares the lower element of `a` and `b` for not-equal.

defs.name: _mm_cvtpd_ps
defs.docs:
Converts packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements in "a" to
 packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements

defs.name: _mm_cvtps_pd
defs.docs:
Converts packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements in `a` to
 packed
 double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements.

defs.name: _mm_cvtpd_epi32
defs.docs:
Converts packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements in `a` to
 packed 32-bit integers.

defs.name: _mm_cvtsd_si32
defs.docs:
Converts the lower double-precision (64-bit) floating-point element in a to
 a 32-bit integer.

defs.name: _mm_cvtsd_ss
defs.docs:
Converts the lower double-precision (64-bit) floating-point element in `b`
 to a single-precision (32-bit) floating-point element, store the result in
 the lower element of the return value, and copies the upper element from `a`
 to the upper element the return value.

defs.name: _mm_cvtsd_f64
defs.docs: Returns the lower double-precision (64-bit) floating-point element of "a".

defs.name: _mm_cvtss_sd
defs.docs:
Converts the lower single-precision (32-bit) floating-point element in `b`
 to a double-precision (64-bit) floating-point element, store the result in
 the lower element of the return value, and copies the upper element from `a`
 to the upper element the return value.

defs.name: _mm_cvttpd_epi32
defs.docs:
Converts packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements in `a` to
 packed 32-bit integers with truncation.

defs.name: _mm_cvttsd_si32
defs.docs:
Converts the lower double-precision (64-bit) floating-point element in `a`
 to a 32-bit integer with truncation.

defs.name: _mm_cvttps_epi32
defs.docs:
Converts packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements in `a` to
 packed 32-bit integers with truncation.

defs.name: _mm_set_sd
defs.docs:
Copies double-precision (64-bit) floating-point element `a` to the lower
 element of the packed 64-bit return value.

defs.name: _mm_set1_pd
defs.docs:
Broadcasts double-precision (64-bit) floating-point value a to all elements
 of the return value.

defs.name: _mm_set_pd1
defs.docs:
Broadcasts double-precision (64-bit) floating-point value a to all elements
 of the return value.

defs.name: _mm_set_pd
defs.docs:
Sets packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements in the return
 value with the supplied values.

defs.name: _mm_setr_pd
defs.docs:
Sets packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements in the return
 value with the supplied values in reverse order.

defs.name: _mm_setzero_pd
defs.docs:
Returns packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements with all
 zeros.

defs.name: _mm_movemask_pd
defs.docs: Returns a mask of the most significant bit of each element in `a`.

defs.name: _mm_load_pd
defs.docs:
Loads 128-bits (composed of 2 packed double-precision (64-bit)
 floating-point elements) from memory into the returned vector.
 `mem_addr` must be aligned on a 16-byte boundary or a general-protection
 exception may be generated.

defs.name: _mm_load_sd
defs.docs:
Loads a 64-bit double-precision value to the low element of a
 128-bit integer vector and clears the upper element.

defs.name: _mm_loadh_pd
defs.docs:
Loads a double-precision value into the high-order bits of a 128-bit
 vector of `[2 x double]`. The low-order bits are copied from the low-order
 bits of the first operand.

defs.name: _mm_loadl_pd
defs.docs:
Loads a double-precision value into the low-order bits of a 128-bit
 vector of `[2 x double]`. The high-order bits are copied from the
 high-order bits of the first operand.

defs.name: _mm_stream_pd
defs.docs:
Stores a 128-bit floating point vector of `[2 x double]` to a 128-bit
 aligned memory location.
 To minimize caching, the data is flagged as non-temporal (unlikely to be
 used again soon).

defs.name: _mm_store_sd
defs.docs:
Stores the lower 64 bits of a 128-bit vector of `[2 x double]` to a
 memory location.

defs.name: _mm_store_pd
defs.docs:
Stores 128-bits (composed of 2 packed double-precision (64-bit)
 floating-point elements) from `a` into memory. `mem_addr` must be aligned
 on a 16-byte boundary or a general-protection exception may be generated.

defs.name: _mm_storeu_pd
defs.docs:
Stores 128-bits (composed of 2 packed double-precision (64-bit)
 floating-point elements) from `a` into memory.
 `mem_addr` does not need to be aligned on any particular boundary.

defs.name: _mm_store1_pd
defs.docs:
Stores the lower double-precision (64-bit) floating-point element from `a`
 into 2 contiguous elements in memory. `mem_addr` must be aligned on a
 16-byte boundary or a general-protection exception may be generated.

defs.name: _mm_store_pd1
defs.docs:
Stores the lower double-precision (64-bit) floating-point element from `a`
 into 2 contiguous elements in memory. `mem_addr` must be aligned on a
 16-byte boundary or a general-protection exception may be generated.

defs.name: _mm_storer_pd
defs.docs:
Stores 2 double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements from `a` into
 memory in reverse order.
 `mem_addr` must be aligned on a 16-byte boundary or a general-protection
 exception may be generated.

defs.name: _mm_storeh_pd
defs.docs:
Stores the upper 64 bits of a 128-bit vector of `[2 x double]` to a
 memory location.

defs.name: _mm_storel_pd
defs.docs:
Stores the lower 64 bits of a 128-bit vector of `[2 x double]` to a
 memory location.

defs.name: _mm_load1_pd
defs.docs:
Loads a double-precision (64-bit) floating-point element from memory
 into both elements of returned vector.

defs.name: _mm_load_pd1
defs.docs:
Loads a double-precision (64-bit) floating-point element from memory
 into both elements of returned vector.

defs.name: _mm_loadr_pd
defs.docs:
Loads 2 double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements from memory into
 the returned vector in reverse order. `mem_addr` must be aligned on a
 16-byte boundary or a general-protection exception may be generated.

defs.name: _mm_loadu_pd
defs.docs:
Loads 128-bits (composed of 2 packed double-precision (64-bit)
 floating-point elements) from memory into the returned vector.
 `mem_addr` does not need to be aligned on any particular boundary.

defs.name: _mm_shuffle_pd
defs.docs:
Constructs a 128-bit floating-point vector of `[2 x double]` from two
 128-bit vector parameters of `[2 x double]`, using the immediate-value
 parameter as a specifier.

defs.name: _mm_move_sd
defs.docs:
Constructs a 128-bit floating-point vector of `[2 x double]`. The lower
 64 bits are set to the lower 64 bits of the second parameter. The upper
 64 bits are set to the upper 64 bits of the first parameter.

defs.name: _mm_castpd_ps
defs.docs:
Casts a 128-bit floating-point vector of `[2 x double]` into a 128-bit
 floating-point vector of `[4 x float]`.

defs.name: _mm_castpd_si128
defs.docs:
Casts a 128-bit floating-point vector of `[2 x double]` into a 128-bit
 integer vector.

defs.name: _mm_castps_pd
defs.docs:
Casts a 128-bit floating-point vector of `[4 x float]` into a 128-bit
 floating-point vector of `[2 x double]`.

defs.name: _mm_castps_si128
defs.docs:
Casts a 128-bit floating-point vector of `[4 x float]` into a 128-bit
 integer vector.

defs.name: _mm_castsi128_pd
defs.docs:
Casts a 128-bit integer vector into a 128-bit floating-point vector
 of `[2 x double]`.

defs.name: _mm_castsi128_ps
defs.docs:
Casts a 128-bit integer vector into a 128-bit floating-point vector
 of `[4 x float]`.

defs.name: _mm_undefined_pd
defs.docs: Returns vector of type __m128d with undefined elements.

defs.name: _mm_undefined_si128
defs.docs: Returns vector of type __m128i with undefined elements.

defs.docs:

 the two `__m128d` interleaved input elements, i.e.:

defs.name: _mm_add_si64
defs.docs:
Adds two signed or unsigned 64-bit integer values, returning the
 lower 64 bits of the sum.

defs.name: _mm_mul_su32
defs.docs:
Multiplies 32-bit unsigned integer values contained in the lower bits
 of the two 64-bit integer vectors and returns the 64-bit unsigned
 product.

defs.name: _mm_sub_si64
defs.docs:
Subtracts signed or unsigned 64-bit integer values and writes the
 difference to the corresponding bits in the destination.

defs.name: _mm_cvtpi32_pd
defs.docs:
Converts the two signed 32-bit integer elements of a 64-bit vector of
 `[2 x i32]` into two double-precision floating-point values, returned in a
 128-bit vector of `[2 x double]`.

defs.name: _mm_set_epi64
defs.docs:
Initializes both 64-bit values in a 128-bit vector of `[2 x i64]` with
 the specified 64-bit integer values.

defs.name: _mm_set1_epi64
defs.docs:
Initializes both values in a 128-bit vector of `[2 x i64]` with the
 specified 64-bit value.

defs.name: _mm_setr_epi64
defs.docs:
Constructs a 128-bit integer vector, initialized in reverse order
 with the specified 64-bit integral values.

defs.name: _mm_movepi64_pi64
defs.docs:
Returns the lower 64 bits of a 128-bit integer vector as a 64-bit
 integer.

defs.name: _mm_movpi64_epi64
defs.docs:
Moves the 64-bit operand to a 128-bit integer vector, zeroing the
 upper bits.

defs.name: _mm_cvtpd_pi32
defs.docs:
Converts the two double-precision floating-point elements of a
 128-bit vector of `[2 x double]` into two signed 32-bit integer values,
 returned in a 64-bit vector of `[2 x i32]`.

defs.name: _mm_cvttpd_pi32
defs.docs:
Converts the two double-precision floating-point elements of a
 128-bit vector of `[2 x double]` into two signed 32-bit integer values,
 returned in a 64-bit vector of `[2 x i32]`.
 If the result of either conversion is inexact, the result is truncated
 (rounded towards zero) regardless of the current MXCSR setting.

defs.name: _mm_addsub_ps
defs.docs:
Alternatively add and subtract packed single-precision (32-bit)
 floating-point elements in `a` to/from packed elements in `b`.

defs.name: _mm_addsub_pd
defs.docs:
Alternatively add and subtract packed double-precision (64-bit)
 floating-point elements in `a` to/from packed elements in `b`.

defs.name: _mm_hadd_pd
defs.docs:
Horizontally adds adjacent pairs of double-precision (64-bit)
 floating-point elements in `a` and `b`, and pack the results.

defs.name: _mm_hadd_ps
defs.docs:
Horizontally adds adjacent pairs of single-precision (32-bit)
 floating-point elements in `a` and `b`, and pack the results.

defs.name: _mm_hsub_pd
defs.docs:
Horizontally subtract adjacent pairs of double-precision (64-bit)
 floating-point elements in `a` and `b`, and pack the results.

defs.name: _mm_hsub_ps
defs.docs:
Horizontally adds adjacent pairs of single-precision (32-bit)
 floating-point elements in `a` and `b`, and pack the results.

defs.name: _mm_lddqu_si128
defs.docs:
Loads 128-bits of integer data from unaligned memory.
 This intrinsic may perform better than `_mm_loadu_si128`
 when the data crosses a cache line boundary.

defs.name: _mm_movedup_pd
defs.docs:
Duplicate the low double-precision (64-bit) floating-point element
 from `a`.

defs.name: _mm_loaddup_pd
defs.docs:
Loads a double-precision (64-bit) floating-point element from memory
 into both elements of return vector.

defs.name: _mm_movehdup_ps
defs.docs:
Duplicate odd-indexed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements
 from `a`.

defs.name: _mm_moveldup_ps
defs.docs:
Duplicate even-indexed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements
 from `a`.

defs.name: _mm_abs_epi8
defs.docs:
Computes the absolute value of packed 8-bit signed integers in `a` and
 return the unsigned results.

defs.name: _mm_abs_epi16
defs.docs:
Computes the absolute value of each of the packed 16-bit signed integers in
 `a` and
 return the 16-bit unsigned integer

defs.name: _mm_abs_epi32
defs.docs:
Computes the absolute value of each of the packed 32-bit signed integers in
 `a` and
 return the 32-bit unsigned integer

defs.name: _mm_shuffle_epi8
defs.docs: Shuffles bytes from `a` according to the content of `b`.

defs.name: _mm_alignr_epi8
defs.docs:
Concatenate 16-byte blocks in `a` and `b` into a 32-byte temporary result,
 shift the result right by `n` bytes, and returns the low 16 bytes.

defs.name: _mm_hadd_epi16
defs.docs:
Horizontally adds the adjacent pairs of values contained in 2 packed
 128-bit vectors of `[8 x i16]`.

defs.name: _mm_hadds_epi16
defs.docs:
Horizontally adds the adjacent pairs of values contained in 2 packed
 128-bit vectors of `[8 x i16]`. Positive sums greater than 7FFFh are
 saturated to 7FFFh. Negative sums less than 8000h are saturated to 8000h.

defs.name: _mm_hadd_epi32
defs.docs:
Horizontally adds the adjacent pairs of values contained in 2 packed
 128-bit vectors of `[4 x i32]`.

defs.name: _mm_hsub_epi16
defs.docs:
Horizontally subtract the adjacent pairs of values contained in 2
 packed 128-bit vectors of `[8 x i16]`.

defs.name: _mm_hsubs_epi16
defs.docs:
Horizontally subtract the adjacent pairs of values contained in 2
 packed 128-bit vectors of `[8 x i16]`. Positive differences greater than
 7FFFh are saturated to 7FFFh. Negative differences less than 8000h are
 saturated to 8000h.

defs.name: _mm_hsub_epi32
defs.docs:
Horizontally subtract the adjacent pairs of values contained in 2
 packed 128-bit vectors of `[4 x i32]`.

defs.name: _mm_maddubs_epi16
defs.docs:
Multiplies corresponding pairs of packed 8-bit unsigned integer
 values contained in the first source operand and packed 8-bit signed
 integer values contained in the second source operand, add pairs of
 contiguous products with signed saturation, and writes the 16-bit sums to
 the corresponding bits in the destination.

defs.name: _mm_mulhrs_epi16
defs.docs:
Multiplies packed 16-bit signed integer values, truncate the 32-bit
 product to the 18 most significant bits by right-shifting, round the
 truncated value by adding 1, and write bits `[16:1]` to the destination.

defs.name: _mm_sign_epi8
defs.docs:
Negates packed 8-bit integers in `a` when the corresponding signed 8-bit
 integer in `b` is negative, and returns the result.
 Elements in result are zeroed out when the corresponding element in `b`
 is zero.

defs.name: _mm_sign_epi16
defs.docs:
Negates packed 16-bit integers in `a` when the corresponding signed 16-bit
 integer in `b` is negative, and returns the results.
 Elements in result are zeroed out when the corresponding element in `b`
 is zero.

defs.name: _mm_sign_epi32
defs.docs:
Negates packed 32-bit integers in `a` when the corresponding signed 32-bit
 integer in `b` is negative, and returns the results.
 Element in result are zeroed out when the corresponding element in `b`
 is zero.

defs.name: _mm_abs_pi8
defs.docs:
Computes the absolute value of packed 8-bit integers in `a` and
 return the unsigned results.

defs.name: _mm_abs_pi16
defs.docs:
Computes the absolute value of packed 8-bit integers in `a`, and returns the
 unsigned results.

defs.name: _mm_abs_pi32
defs.docs:
Computes the absolute value of packed 32-bit integers in `a`, and returns the
 unsigned results.

defs.name: _mm_shuffle_pi8
defs.docs:
Shuffles packed 8-bit integers in `a` according to shuffle control mask in
 the corresponding 8-bit element of `b`, and returns the results

defs.name: _mm_alignr_pi8
defs.docs:
Concatenates the two 64-bit integer vector operands, and right-shifts
 the result by the number of bytes specified in the immediate operand.

defs.name: _mm_hadd_pi16
defs.docs:
Horizontally adds the adjacent pairs of values contained in 2 packed
 64-bit vectors of `[4 x i16]`.

defs.name: _mm_hadd_pi32
defs.docs:
Horizontally adds the adjacent pairs of values contained in 2 packed
 64-bit vectors of `[2 x i32]`.

defs.name: _mm_hadds_pi16
defs.docs:
Horizontally adds the adjacent pairs of values contained in 2 packed
 64-bit vectors of `[4 x i16]`. Positive sums greater than 7FFFh are
 saturated to 7FFFh. Negative sums less than 8000h are saturated to 8000h.

defs.name: _mm_hsub_pi16
defs.docs:
Horizontally subtracts the adjacent pairs of values contained in 2
 packed 64-bit vectors of `[4 x i16]`.

defs.name: _mm_hsub_pi32
defs.docs:
Horizontally subtracts the adjacent pairs of values contained in 2
 packed 64-bit vectors of `[2 x i32]`.

defs.name: _mm_hsubs_pi16
defs.docs:
Horizontally subtracts the adjacent pairs of values contained in 2
 packed 64-bit vectors of `[4 x i16]`. Positive differences greater than
 7FFFh are saturated to 7FFFh. Negative differences less than 8000h are
 saturated to 8000h.

defs.name: _mm_maddubs_pi16
defs.docs:
Multiplies corresponding pairs of packed 8-bit unsigned integer
 values contained in the first source operand and packed 8-bit signed
 integer values contained in the second source operand, adds pairs of
 contiguous products with signed saturation, and writes the 16-bit sums to
 the corresponding bits in the destination.

defs.name: _mm_mulhrs_pi16
defs.docs:
Multiplies packed 16-bit signed integer values, truncates the 32-bit
 products to the 18 most significant bits by right-shifting, rounds the
 truncated value by adding 1, and writes bits `[16:1]` to the destination.

defs.name: _mm_sign_pi8
defs.docs:
Negates packed 8-bit integers in `a` when the corresponding signed 8-bit
 integer in `b` is negative, and returns the results.
 Element in result are zeroed out when the corresponding element in `b` is
 zero.

defs.name: _mm_sign_pi16
defs.docs:
Negates packed 16-bit integers in `a` when the corresponding signed 16-bit
 integer in `b` is negative, and returns the results.
 Element in result are zeroed out when the corresponding element in `b` is
 zero.

defs.name: _mm_sign_pi32
defs.docs:
Negates packed 32-bit integers in `a` when the corresponding signed 32-bit
 integer in `b` is negative, and returns the results.
 Element in result are zeroed out when the corresponding element in `b` is
 zero.

defs.name: _MM_FROUND_TO_NEG_INF

use MXCSR.RC and do not suppress exceptions; see

defs.name: _MM_FROUND_NEARBYINT
defs.docs: use MXCSR.RC and suppress exceptions; see `vendor::_MM_SET_ROUNDING_MODE`

defs.name: _mm_blendv_epi8
defs.docs: Blend packed 8-bit integers from `a` and `b` using `mask`

defs.name: _mm_blend_epi16
defs.docs: Blend packed 16-bit integers from `a` and `b` using the mask `imm8`.

defs.name: _mm_blendv_pd
defs.docs:
Blend packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements from `a`
 and `b` using `mask`

defs.name: _mm_blendv_ps
defs.docs:
Blend packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements from `a`
 and `b` using `mask`

defs.name: _mm_blend_pd
defs.docs:
Blend packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements from `a`
 and `b` using control mask `imm2`

defs.name: _mm_blend_ps
defs.docs:
Blend packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements from `a`
 and `b` using mask `imm4`

defs.name: _mm_extract_ps
defs.docs:
Extracts a single-precision (32-bit) floating-point element from `a`,
 selected with `imm8`

defs.name: _mm_extract_epi8
defs.docs:
Extracts an 8-bit integer from `a`, selected with `imm8`. Returns a 32-bit
 integer containing the zero-extended integer data.

defs.name: _mm_extract_epi32
defs.docs: Extracts an 32-bit integer from `a` selected with `imm8`

defs.name: _mm_insert_ps
defs.docs:
Select a single value in `a` to store at some position in `b`,
 Then zero elements according to `imm8`.

defs.name: _mm_insert_epi8
defs.docs:
Returns a copy of `a` with the 8-bit integer from `i` inserted at a
 location specified by `imm8`.

defs.name: _mm_insert_epi32
defs.docs:
Returns a copy of `a` with the 32-bit integer from `i` inserted at a
 location specified by `imm8`.

defs.name: _mm_max_epi8
defs.docs:
Compares packed 8-bit integers in `a` and `b` and returns packed maximum
 values in dst.

defs.name: _mm_max_epu16
defs.docs:
Compares packed unsigned 16-bit integers in `a` and `b`, and returns packed
 maximum.

defs.name: _mm_max_epi32
defs.docs:
Compares packed 32-bit integers in `a` and `b`, and returns packed maximum
 values.

defs.name: _mm_max_epu32
defs.docs:
Compares packed unsigned 32-bit integers in `a` and `b`, and returns packed
 maximum values.

defs.name: _mm_min_epi8
defs.docs:
Compares packed 8-bit integers in `a` and `b` and returns packed minimum
 values in dst.

defs.name: _mm_min_epu16
defs.docs:
Compares packed unsigned 16-bit integers in `a` and `b`, and returns packed
 minimum.

defs.name: _mm_min_epi32
defs.docs:
Compares packed 32-bit integers in `a` and `b`, and returns packed minimum
 values.

defs.name: _mm_min_epu32
defs.docs:
Compares packed unsigned 32-bit integers in `a` and `b`, and returns packed
 minimum values.

defs.name: _mm_packus_epi32
defs.docs:
Converts packed 32-bit integers from `a` and `b` to packed 16-bit integers
 using unsigned saturation

defs.name: _mm_cmpeq_epi64
defs.docs: Compares packed 64-bit integers in `a` and `b` for equality

defs.name: _mm_cvtepi8_epi16

defs.name: _mm_cvtepi8_epi32
defs.docs: Sign extend packed 8-bit integers in `a` to packed 32-bit integers

defs.name: _mm_cvtepi8_epi64

Sign extend packed 8-bit integers in the low 8 bytes of `a` to packed
 64-bit integers

defs.name: _mm_cvtepi16_epi32
defs.docs: Sign extend packed 16-bit integers in `a` to packed 32-bit integers

defs.name: _mm_cvtepi16_epi64
defs.docs: Sign extend packed 16-bit integers in `a` to packed 64-bit integers

defs.name: _mm_cvtepi32_epi64
defs.docs: Sign extend packed 32-bit integers in `a` to packed 64-bit integers

defs.name: _mm_cvtepu8_epi16
defs.docs: Zeroes extend packed unsigned 8-bit integers in `a` to packed 16-bit integers

defs.name: _mm_cvtepu8_epi32
defs.docs: Zeroes extend packed unsigned 8-bit integers in `a` to packed 32-bit integers

defs.name: _mm_cvtepu8_epi64
defs.docs: Zeroes extend packed unsigned 8-bit integers in `a` to packed 64-bit integers

defs.name: _mm_cvtepu16_epi32
defs.docs:
Zeroes extend packed unsigned 16-bit integers in `a`
 to packed 32-bit integers

defs.name: _mm_cvtepu16_epi64
defs.docs:
Zeroes extend packed unsigned 16-bit integers in `a`
 to packed 64-bit integers

defs.name: _mm_cvtepu32_epi64
defs.docs:
Zeroes extend packed unsigned 32-bit integers in `a`
 to packed 64-bit integers

defs.name: _mm_dp_pd
defs.docs: Returns the dot product of two __m128d vectors.

defs.name: _mm_dp_ps
defs.docs: Returns the dot product of two __m128 vectors.

defs.name: _mm_floor_pd
defs.docs:
Round the packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements in `a`
 down to an integer value, and stores the results as packed double-precision
 floating-point elements.

defs.name: _mm_floor_ps
defs.docs:
Round the packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements in `a`
 down to an integer value, and stores the results as packed single-precision
 floating-point elements.

defs.name: _mm_floor_sd
defs.docs:
Round the lower double-precision (64-bit) floating-point element in `b`
 down to an integer value, store the result as a double-precision
 floating-point element in the lower element of the intrinsic result,
 and copies the upper element from `a` to the upper element of the intrinsic
 result.

defs.name: _mm_floor_ss
defs.docs:
Round the lower single-precision (32-bit) floating-point element in `b`
 down to an integer value, store the result as a single-precision
 floating-point element in the lower element of the intrinsic result,
 and copies the upper 3 packed elements from `a` to the upper elements
 of the intrinsic result.

defs.name: _mm_ceil_pd
defs.docs:
Round the packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements in `a`
 up to an integer value, and stores the results as packed double-precision
 floating-point elements.

defs.name: _mm_ceil_ps
defs.docs:
Round the packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements in `a`
 up to an integer value, and stores the results as packed single-precision
 floating-point elements.

defs.name: _mm_ceil_sd
defs.docs:
Round the lower double-precision (64-bit) floating-point element in `b`
 up to an integer value, store the result as a double-precision
 floating-point element in the lower element of the intrisic result,
 and copies the upper element from `a` to the upper element
 of the intrinsic result.

defs.name: _mm_ceil_ss
defs.docs:
Round the lower single-precision (32-bit) floating-point element in `b`
 up to an integer value, store the result as a single-precision
 floating-point element in the lower element of the intrinsic result,
 and copies the upper 3 packed elements from `a` to the upper elements
 of the intrinsic result.

defs.name: _mm_round_pd
defs.docs:
Round the packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements in `a`
 using the `rounding` parameter, and stores the results as packed
 double-precision floating-point elements.
 Rounding is done according to the rounding parameter, which can be one of:

defs.name: _mm_round_ps
defs.docs:
Round the packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements in `a`
 using the `rounding` parameter, and stores the results as packed
 single-precision floating-point elements.
 Rounding is done according to the rounding parameter, which can be one of:

defs.name: _mm_round_sd
defs.docs:
Round the lower double-precision (64-bit) floating-point element in `b`
 using the `rounding` parameter, store the result as a double-precision
 floating-point element in the lower element of the intrinsic result,
 and copies the upper element from `a` to the upper element of the intrinsic
 result.
 Rounding is done according to the rounding parameter, which can be one of:

defs.docs:
Round the lower single-precision (32-bit) floating-point element in `b`
 using the `rounding` parameter, store the result as a single-precision

 and copies the upper 3 packed elements from `a` to the upper elements
 of the instrinsic result.
 Rounding is done according to the rounding parameter, which can be one of:

defs.name: _mm_minpos_epu16
defs.docs:
Finds the minimum unsigned 16-bit element in the 128-bit __m128i vector,
 returning a vector containing its value in its first position, and its
 index
 in its second position; all other elements are set to zero.

defs.name: _mm_mul_epi32
defs.docs:
Multiplies the low 32-bit integers from each packed 64-bit
 element in `a` and `b`, and returns the signed 64-bit result.

defs.name: _mm_mullo_epi32
defs.docs:
Multiplies the packed 32-bit integers in `a` and `b`, producing intermediate
 64-bit integers, and returns the lowest 32-bit, whatever they might be,
 reinterpreted as a signed integer. While `pmulld __m128i::splat(2),
 __m128i::splat(2)` returns the obvious `__m128i::splat(4)`, due to wrapping
 arithmetic `pmulld __m128i::splat(i32::MAX), __m128i::splat(2)` would
 return a negative number.

defs.name: _mm_mpsadbw_epu8
defs.docs:
Subtracts 8-bit unsigned integer values and computes the absolute
 values of the differences to the corresponding bits in the destination.
 Then sums of the absolute differences are returned according to the bit
 fields in the immediate operand.

defs.name: _mm_testz_si128
defs.docs:
Tests whether the specified bits in a 128-bit integer vector are all
 zeros.

defs.name: _mm_testc_si128
defs.docs:
Tests whether the specified bits in a 128-bit integer vector are all
 ones.

defs.name: _mm_testnzc_si128
defs.docs:
Tests whether the specified bits in a 128-bit integer vector are
 neither all zeros nor all ones.

defs.name: _mm_test_all_zeros
defs.docs:
Tests whether the specified bits in a 128-bit integer vector are all
 zeros.

defs.name: _mm_test_all_ones
defs.docs:
Tests whether the specified bits in `a` 128-bit integer vector are all
 ones.

defs.name: _mm_test_mix_ones_zeros
defs.docs:
Tests whether the specified bits in a 128-bit integer vector are
 neither all zeros nor all ones.

defs.name: _SIDD_UBYTE_OPS
defs.docs: String contains unsigned 8-bit characters *(Default)*

defs.name: _SIDD_UWORD_OPS
defs.docs: String contains unsigned 16-bit characters

defs.name: _SIDD_SBYTE_OPS
defs.docs: String contains signed 8-bit characters

defs.name: _SIDD_SWORD_OPS
defs.docs: String contains unsigned 16-bit characters

defs.name: _SIDD_CMP_EQUAL_ANY
defs.docs: For each character in `a`, find if it is in `b` *(Default)*

defs.name: _SIDD_CMP_RANGES
defs.docs:
For each character in `a`, determine if
 `b[0] <= c <= b[1] or b[1] <= c <= b[2]...`

defs.name: _SIDD_CMP_EQUAL_EACH
defs.docs: The strings defined by `a` and `b` are equal

defs.name: _SIDD_CMP_EQUAL_ORDERED
defs.docs: Search for the defined substring in the target

defs.name: _SIDD_POSITIVE_POLARITY
defs.docs: Do not negate results *(Default)*

defs.name: _SIDD_NEGATIVE_POLARITY
defs.docs: Negates results

defs.name: _SIDD_MASKED_POSITIVE_POLARITY
defs.docs: Do not negate results before the end of the string

defs.name: _SIDD_MASKED_NEGATIVE_POLARITY
defs.docs: Negates results only before the end of the string

defs.name: _SIDD_LEAST_SIGNIFICANT
defs.docs: **Index only**: return the least significant bit *(Default)*

defs.name: _SIDD_MOST_SIGNIFICANT
defs.docs: **Index only**: return the most significant bit

defs.name: _SIDD_BIT_MASK
defs.docs: **Mask only**: return the bit mask

defs.name: _SIDD_UNIT_MASK
defs.docs: **Mask only**: return the byte mask

defs.name: _mm_cmpistrm
defs.docs:
Compares packed strings with implicit lengths in `a` and `b` using the
 control in `imm8`, and return the generated mask.

defs.name: _mm_cmpistri
defs.docs:
Compares packed strings with implicit lengths in `a` and `b` using the
 control in `imm8` and return the generated index. Similar to
 [`_mm_cmpestri`] with the exception that [`_mm_cmpestri`] requires the
 lengths of `a` and `b` to be explicitly specified.

defs.name: _mm_cmpistrz
defs.docs:
Compares packed strings with implicit lengths in `a` and `b` using the
 control in `imm8`, and return `1` if any character in `b` was null.
 and `0` otherwise.

defs.name: _mm_cmpistrc
defs.docs:
Compares packed strings with implicit lengths in `a` and `b` using the
 control in `imm8`, and return `1` if the resulting mask was non-zero,
 and `0` otherwise.

defs.name: _mm_cmpistrs
defs.docs:
Compares packed strings with implicit lengths in `a` and `b` using the
 control in `imm8`, and returns `1` if any character in `a` was null,
 and `0` otherwise.

defs.name: _mm_cmpistro
defs.docs:
Compares packed strings with implicit lengths in `a` and `b` using the
 control in `imm8`, and return bit `0` of the resulting bit mask.

defs.name: _mm_cmpistra
defs.docs:
Compares packed strings with implicit lengths in `a` and `b` using the
 control in `imm8`, and return `1` if `b` did not contain a null
 character and the resulting mask was zero, and `0` otherwise.

defs.name: _mm_cmpestrm
defs.docs:
Compares packed strings in `a` and `b` with lengths `la` and `lb`
 using the control in `imm8`, and return the generated mask.

defs.name: _mm_cmpestri
defs.docs:
Compares packed strings `a` and `b` with lengths `la` and `lb` using the
 control in `imm8` and return the generated index. Similar to
 [`_mm_cmpistri`] with the exception that [`_mm_cmpistri`] implicitly
 determines the length of `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpestrz
defs.docs:
Compares packed strings in `a` and `b` with lengths `la` and `lb`
 using the control in `imm8`, and return `1` if any character in
 `b` was null, and `0` otherwise.

defs.name: _mm_cmpestrc
defs.docs:
Compares packed strings in `a` and `b` with lengths `la` and `lb`
 using the control in `imm8`, and return `1` if the resulting mask
 was non-zero, and `0` otherwise.

defs.name: _mm_cmpestrs
defs.docs:
Compares packed strings in `a` and `b` with lengths `la` and `lb`
 using the control in `imm8`, and return `1` if any character in
 a was null, and `0` otherwise.

defs.name: _mm_cmpestro
defs.docs:
Compares packed strings in `a` and `b` with lengths `la` and `lb`
 using the control in `imm8`, and return bit `0` of the resulting
 bit mask.

defs.name: _mm_cmpestra
defs.docs:
Compares packed strings in `a` and `b` with lengths `la` and `lb`
 using the control in `imm8`, and return `1` if `b` did not
 contain a null character and the resulting mask was zero, and `0`
 otherwise.

defs.name: _mm_crc32_u8
defs.docs:
Starting with the initial value in `crc`, return the accumulated
 CRC32 value for unsigned 8-bit integer `v`.

defs.name: _mm_crc32_u16
defs.docs:
Starting with the initial value in `crc`, return the accumulated
 CRC32 value for unsigned 16-bit integer `v`.

defs.name: _mm_crc32_u32
defs.docs:
Starting with the initial value in `crc`, return the accumulated
 CRC32 value for unsigned 32-bit integer `v`.

defs.name: _mm_cmpgt_epi64
defs.docs:
Compares packed 64-bit integers in `a` and `b` for greater-than,
 return the results.

defs.name: _mm256_add_pd
defs.docs:
Adds packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements
 in `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm256_add_ps
defs.docs:
Adds packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements in `a` and
 `b`.

defs.name: _mm256_and_pd

Computes the bitwise AND of a packed double-precision (64-bit)
 floating-point elements in `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm256_and_ps
defs.docs:
Computes the bitwise AND of packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point
 elements in `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm256_or_pd
defs.docs:
Computes the bitwise OR packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point
 elements in `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm256_or_ps
defs.docs:
Computes the bitwise OR packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point
 elements in `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm256_shuffle_pd

defs.name: _mm256_shuffle_ps
defs.docs:
Shuffles single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements in `a` within
 128-bit lanes using the control in `imm8`.

defs.name: _mm256_andnot_pd

Computes the bitwise NOT of packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point
 elements in `a`, and then AND with `b`.

defs.name: _mm256_andnot_ps
defs.docs:
Computes the bitwise NOT of packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point
 elements in `a`
 and then AND with `b`.

defs.name: _mm256_max_pd
defs.docs:
Compares packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements
 in `a` and `b`, and returns packed maximum values

defs.name: _mm256_max_ps
defs.docs:
Compares packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements in `a`
 and `b`, and returns packed maximum values

defs.name: _mm256_min_pd
defs.docs:
Compares packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements
 in `a` and `b`, and returns packed minimum values

defs.name: _mm256_min_ps
defs.docs:
Compares packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements in `a`
 and `b`, and returns packed minimum values

defs.name: _mm256_mul_pd
defs.docs:
Multiplies packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements
 in `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm256_mul_ps
defs.docs:
Multiplies packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements in `a` and
 `b`.

defs.name: _mm256_addsub_pd
defs.docs:
Alternatively adds and subtracts packed double-precision (64-bit)
 floating-point elements in `a` to/from packed elements in `b`.

defs.name: _mm256_addsub_ps
defs.docs:
Alternatively adds and subtracts packed single-precision (32-bit)
 floating-point elements in `a` to/from packed elements in `b`.

defs.name: _mm256_sub_pd
defs.docs:
Subtracts packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements in `b`
 from packed elements in `a`.

defs.name: _mm256_sub_ps
defs.docs:
Subtracts packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements in `b`
 from packed elements in `a`.

defs.name: _mm256_div_ps
defs.docs:
Computes the division of each of the 8 packed 32-bit floating-point elements
 in `a` by the corresponding packed elements in `b`.

defs.name: _mm256_div_pd
defs.docs:
Computes the division of each of the 4 packed 64-bit floating-point elements
 in `a` by the corresponding packed elements in `b`.

defs.name: _mm256_round_pd
defs.docs:
Rounds packed double-precision (64-bit) floating point elements in `a`
 according to the flag `b`. The value of `b` may be as follows:

defs.name: _mm256_ceil_pd
defs.docs:
Rounds packed double-precision (64-bit) floating point elements in `a`
 toward positive infinity.

defs.name: _mm256_floor_pd
defs.docs:
Rounds packed double-precision (64-bit) floating point elements in `a`
 toward negative infinity.

defs.name: _mm256_round_ps
defs.docs:
Rounds packed single-precision (32-bit) floating point elements in `a`
 according to the flag `b`. The value of `b` may be as follows:

defs.name: _mm256_ceil_ps
defs.docs:
Rounds packed single-precision (32-bit) floating point elements in `a`
 toward positive infinity.

defs.name: _mm256_floor_ps
defs.docs:
Rounds packed single-precision (32-bit) floating point elements in `a`
 toward negative infinity.

defs.name: _mm256_sqrt_ps
defs.docs:
Returns the square root of packed single-precision (32-bit) floating point
 elements in `a`.

defs.name: _mm256_sqrt_pd
defs.docs:
Returns the square root of packed double-precision (64-bit) floating point
 elements in `a`.

defs.name: _mm256_blend_pd
defs.docs:
Blends packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements from
 `a` and `b` using control mask `imm8`.

defs.name: _mm256_blend_ps
defs.docs:
Blends packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements from
 `a` and `b` using control mask `imm8`.

defs.name: _mm256_blendv_pd
defs.docs:
Blends packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements from
 `a` and `b` using `c` as a mask.

defs.name: _mm256_blendv_ps
defs.docs:
Blends packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements from
 `a` and `b` using `c` as a mask.

defs.name: _mm256_dp_ps
defs.docs:
Conditionally multiplies the packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point
 elements in `a` and `b` using the high 4 bits in `imm8`,
 sum the four products, and conditionally return the sum
  using the low 4 bits of `imm8`.

defs.name: _mm256_hadd_pd
defs.docs:
Horizontal addition of adjacent pairs in the two packed vectors
 of 4 64-bit floating points `a` and `b`.
 In the result, sums of elements from `a` are returned in even locations,
 while sums of elements from `b` are returned in odd locations.

defs.name: _mm256_hadd_ps
defs.docs:
Horizontal addition of adjacent pairs in the two packed vectors
 of 8 32-bit floating points `a` and `b`.
 In the result, sums of elements from `a` are returned in locations of
 indices 0, 1, 4, 5; while sums of elements from `b` are locations
 2, 3, 6, 7.

defs.name: _mm256_hsub_pd
defs.docs:
Horizontal subtraction of adjacent pairs in the two packed vectors
 of 4 64-bit floating points `a` and `b`.
 In the result, sums of elements from `a` are returned in even locations,
 while sums of elements from `b` are returned in odd locations.

defs.name: _mm256_hsub_ps
defs.docs:
Horizontal subtraction of adjacent pairs in the two packed vectors
 of 8 32-bit floating points `a` and `b`.
 In the result, sums of elements from `a` are returned in locations of
 indices 0, 1, 4, 5; while sums of elements from `b` are locations
 2, 3, 6, 7.

defs.name: _mm256_xor_pd
defs.docs:
Computes the bitwise XOR of packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point
 elements in `a` and `b`.

defs.name: _mm256_xor_ps
defs.docs:
Computes the bitwise XOR of packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point
 elements in `a` and `b`.
